      {
        "id": 3069730,
        "name": "John McDermott",
        "username": "John_McDermott",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/43a26b/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2021-01-13T00:32:29.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"167266\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Hold Pegau in any case, it\u2019s a 25+ y wine.<br>\nDrink Trebbiano first.</p>\n<p>What I don t get: you HAVE to drink 2 of 3?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>FWIW, I had dinner at a restaurant last year that had no corkage if you bought a bottle at the wine shop next-door.  Picked up a 2016 Pegau Reserve, and it was fantastic.  Totally agree that it can be held for the long-haul, but it drinks well even young.</p>",
