      {
        "id": 3069759,
        "name": "Sean Corbett",
        "username": "Sean_Corbett",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/sean_corbett/{size}/3384_2.png",
        "created_at": "2021-01-13T01:02:31.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Thanks all.</p>\n<p>From this and from offline convos, it seems like the Cosme Gigondas will be consumed first.</p>\n<p>And from there I need to decide between the Valentini or the Pegau.</p>\n<p>Does Pegau tend to go through a dumb/closed phase?</p>",
